thread.title: U.S. Jobless Claims Fell Last Week

author: Sharon Nunn
title: U.S. Jobless Claims Fell Last Week
text:
WASHINGTONâ€”The number of Americans filing applications for new unemployment benefits fell last week, remaining near historically low levels.
Initial jobless claims, a proxy for layoffs across the U.S., declined by 1,000 to a seasonally adjusted 230,000 in the week ended Jan. 27, the Labor Department said Thursday. Economists surveyed by The Wall Street Journal expected 235,000 new claims last week.
